            <bug_when>2014-10-02 15:40:04 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>If you use the @link API documentation within the qxWeb class to link member functions for the API documentation the &#39;api-verify&#39; job does output a warning.

E.g. use the following &quot;{@link #debug}&quot; in your API documentation and the output at the console will be &quot;Warning: qxWeb: Unknown link target: &#39;#debug&#39;&quot;.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>41719</commentid>
            <who name="Daniel Wagner">daniel.wagner</who>
            <bug_when>2014-11-26 15:17:13 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>This warning is correct since The {@link #methodName} is only intended for targets in the same class (as opposed to module). For methods that are attached to qxWeb, you can use the fully qualified name, e.q. {@link my.cool.Class#debug}. This format is understood by both the qx.Website and qx.Desktop API viewers.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
      
      

